GridTracker 2 (mode tables, WPX-prefix algorithm, logbook-upload edge cases,
Pushover alert send)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

`grayline_server.py::_send_pushover` — port of `sendPushOverAlert()` from
                                src/renderer/lib/roster/sendAlerts.js (POST to
                                api.pushover.net/1/messages.json with user/token/
                                title/message)
`data/modes.json`            — verbatim copy of resources/data/modes.json
`data/modes-phone.json`      — verbatim copy of resources/data/modes-phone.json
`worked_state.py::wpx_prefix` — algorithmic port of `getWpx()` from
                                src/renderer/lib/gtCommon.js
`logbook_uploads.py`          — QRZ response parsing edge cases (RESULT vs
                                STATUS field, AUTH/FAIL distinction, EXTENDED
                                preference, "outside date range" message),
                                ClubLog HTTP-200-as-success heuristic, and the
                                one-retry-on-timeout pattern, all lifted from
                                src/renderer/lib/adif.js (qrzSendLogResult,
                                clubLogQsoResult, postRetryErrorCallaback)
`lotw_fetch.py`               — LoTW download URL parameter set, the
                                qso_qslsince incremental cursor model, the
                                APP_LOTW_RXQSL "+1 second past max" cursor-bump,
                                and the "password incorrect" auth-failure check,
                                all lifted from src/renderer/lib/adif.js
                                (grabLoTWQSL, lotwCallback) and
                                src/renderer/lib/adifWorker.js (APP_LOTW_RXQSL
                                handling at lines 131-143).
`worked_state.py`             — LoTW-confirmed-via-APP_LOTW_RXQSL rule and
                                LOTW_QSL_RCVD == "Y"/"V" semantics lifted from
                                src/renderer/lib/adifWorker.js:295-314.
`logbook_uploads.py::upload_lotw`
                              — TQSL invocation flag set (-a all -l <station>
                                -q -x -d -u) and the "Final Status: Success"
                                success-detection rule lifted from
                                src/renderer/lib/adif.js:2074-2107 (the
                                queueLogToTqsl handler).

Source: https://gitlab.com/gridtracker.org/gridtracker2

